502

lacks the a priori knowledge of St. Sophia. Plotinus/Gnosticism/Paulline Xtianity/Iranian influence: the dialectic. But if I had to chose I'd chose Plotinus. Plus Gnostic overtones due to Heidegger (esp. the Ur-Angst + the role, the crucial role, it plays in authentic being. I researched Plotinus; there is no doubt it is Neo-Platonist. No other doctrines are necessary nor do they apply. My 5 levels are his. Q.E.D. There was a Fall. - 4:30 a.m.: I didn't just realize world

